    <!-- Daily reflections: all original copy (no licensing), one per day via epochDay modulo -->
    <string-array name="daily_quotes">
        <item>Every urge you outlast teaches your brain a new ending.</item>
        <item>You are not starting over. You are starting stronger.</item>
        <item>The craving is loud because it is losing.</item>
        <item>Progress is quiet. Keep making it.</item>
        <item>One honest day is worth more than a perfect week imagined.</item>
        <item>Discomfort is the feeling of rewiring.</item>
        <item>Urges peak, then pass. You only have to outlast the peak.</item>
        <item>Small promises kept build unshakable trust — with yourself.</item>
        <item>You can\'t control the wave, but you\'re learning to surf.</item>
        <item>Today\'s boredom is tomorrow\'s peace, in disguise.</item>
        <item>Healing isn\'t linear. It\'s still healing.</item>
        <item>Every clean morning is proof, not luck.</item>
        <item>You are allowed to find this hard and do it anyway.</item>
        <item>Your attention is the most valuable thing you own. Reclaim it.</item>
        <item>The streak is a side effect. The real win is who you\'re becoming.</item>
        <item>The number grows on its own. Your job is just today.</item>
        <item>Freedom feels like this: choosing, not being chosen for.</item>
        <item>A slip is a data point, not a verdict.</item>
        <item>Rest is part of recovery, not a break from it.</item>
        <item>What you water grows. Stop watering the weeds.</item>
        <item>Cravings are old echoes. You\'re writing new sound.</item>
        <item>Real strength is asking for the tools before you need them.</item>
        <item>Tonight\'s sleep is tomorrow\'s willpower.</item>
        <item>Your hardest days so far all ended. This one will too.</item>
        <item>Quiet consistency beats loud intensity.</item>
        <item>You noticed the urge. That awareness is already a win.</item>
        <item>Two minutes of writing can defuse an hour of wanting.</item>
        <item>Be the person your first milestone believes you are.</item>
    </string-array>

